   First Gov site The MCH Training Program: An Evaluation Executive
   Summary
   This summary assesses the program's accomplishments, identify problems,
   and provide recommendations focused on program operations and
   management.
   Traumatic Brain Injury in the United States: Assessing Outcomes in
   Children: Summary and Recommendations from the Expert Working Group,
   Atlanta GA October 26-27, 2000
   This report summarizes the recommendations from the expert work group
   of researchers, advocates, and other professionals from the United
   States and New Zealand convened October 26-27, 2000 to discuss
   "Methodological Issues in Assessing Outcomes of TBI in Children and
   Youth." The work group identified variables to measure longer-term
   outcomes of TBI in children and youth (ages 0-16); considered the
   strengths and weaknesses of available measures of these outcomes for
   this population; and offered ways to improve measurement, data
   analysis, and terminology used in the study of TBI.
   Title V: A Snapshot of Maternal and Child Health 2000
   Book provides a brief overview of the mission, funding, and framework
   of the Maternal and Child Health Block Grant Program. It also contains
   the current maternal and child health challenges and projects around
   the United States. The status of maternal and child health such as rate
   of suicide, rate of births, population data, children in poverty,
   working mothers, child care are all topics included in this report.
   Diario de salud: La madre, El bebe (Health Diary: Myself, My Baby)--in
   Spanish
   Diary contains information on childbirth from conception to age 2.
   Includes sections for the mother's notes.

